The paper discusses the tradeoff between parallelism and communication cost in a map-reduce computation, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also analyzes the communication cost for solving various problems, such as finding pairs of strings and matrix multiplication, which are related to data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper introduces a model for analyzing the communication cost, which involves information theory (cs.IT).
